title: Local sports digest: No. 11 Stanford women's volleyball tops No. 4 Washington
text:
Local sports digest: No. 11 Stanford women's volleyball tops No. 4 Washington Bay Area News Group Posted: 10/21/2015 10:18:38  28:02 PM PDT Hayley Hodson had 25 kills to help the No. 11 Stanford women's volleyball team rally past No. 4 Washington on Wednesday night at Maples Pavilion. 
The Cardinal won 24-26, 25-19, 16-25, 25-20, 15-13 in its first meeting against Washington since last November, when the Huskies snapped Stanford's school-record 28-match winning streak to start a season. 
Stanford (12-5, 6-3 Pac-12) bounced back after splitting its trip to Utah and Colorado, dropping to its lowest ranking in the AVCA poll since Sept. 28, 2009 when it was also No. 11. Swimming Seven current or past Cal swimmers were among the 36 athletes named to the Team USA squad for December's Duel in the Pool against a squad of European stars. 
Cal senior Josh Prenot and former Bears Nathan Adrian and Tom Shields were named to the men's squad. Current Cal men's associate head coach Yuri Suguiyama will serve as an assistant for the U.S. Former Bears Natalie Coughlin, Missy Franklin, Caitlin Leverenz and Jessica Hardy were named to the women's squad. 
Team USA includes 11 Olympic medalists, but gold medalists Michael Phelps and Katie Ledecky, a Stanford recruit, are not competing at the event. Team Europe's roster will be announced next week. Barracuda Bryan Lerg and Scott Timmins scored first-period goals to give San Jose a 2-0 lead, but the San Diego Gulls rallied to force overtime and then scored the only goal in the shootout to send the Barracuda to a 3-2 American Hockey League loss.
